#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Do you need Networking?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "Who can do without?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Generally, you don't need a working network connection to install Gentoo using\n"
"either the Universal InstallCD or the Installer LiveCD. However, there are some\n"
"circumstances where you do want to have a working Internet connection:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:28
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The stage3 files that are stored in the Universal InstallCD do not \n"
"    match your architecture and you need to download the correct stage3 file\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:32
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    The stage3 file that is generated by the Installer LiveCD does not\n"
"    match your architecture and you need to download the correct stage3 file\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You need to install a specific networking application that will allow you to\n"
"    connect to the Internet which isn't available on the Universal InstallCD or\n"
"    the Installer LiveCD, but is supported by the CD (i.e. you can connect to\n"
"    the Internet using the CD but the necessary sources are not available on\n"
"    the CD)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:43
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You want remote assistance during the installation (using SSH or through\n"
"    direct conversations using IRC)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:51
#, no-wrap
msgid "Do I need Networking?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:55
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To find out if the stage3 file for your architecture is available and you are\n"
"using a Universal InstallCD, take a look inside <path>/mnt/cdrom/stages</path>\n"
"and check if one of the available stages matches your architecture. If not, you\n"
"can still opt for a stage3 file of an architecture compatible with yours.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:62
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The stage3 file built by the x86 Installer LiveCD is optimized for i686 or\n"
"better and uses NPTL.  The stage3 file built by the amd64 Installer LiveCD is\n"
"optimized for generic amd64 usage and uses NPTL.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you, on the other hand, want to use a stage3 file optimized for your\n"
"architecture and the stage3 file of your choice is not available, then you will\n"
"need networking to download the appropriate stage3 file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:74
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"So, if you don't need networking, you can skip the rest of this chapter and \n"
"continue with <uri link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=4\">Preparing the Disks</uri>.\n"
"Otherwise, continue with the networking configuration sections below.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Automatic Network Detection"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "Maybe it just works?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:89
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your system is plugged into an Ethernet network with a DHCP server, it is \n"
"very likely that your networking configuration has already been set up \n"
"automatically for you. If so, you should be able to take advantage of the many\n"
"included network-aware commands on the Installation CD such as <c>ssh</c>, \n"
"<c>scp</c>, <c>ping</c>, <c>irssi</c>, <c>wget</c> and <c>links</c>, among \n"
"others.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:98
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If networking has been configured for you, the <c>/sbin/ifconfig</c> command\n"
"should list some network interfaces besides lo, such as eth0:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:102
#, no-wrap
msgid "/sbin/ifconfig for a working network configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:103
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>/sbin/ifconfig</i>\n"
"<comment>(...)</comment>\n"
"eth0      Link encap:Ethernet  HWaddr 00:50:BA:8F:61:7A\n"
"          inet addr:192.168.0.2  Bcast:192.168.0.255  Mask:255.255.255.0\n"
"          inet6 addr: fe80::50:ba8f:617a/10 Scope:Link\n"
"          UP BROADCAST RUNNING MULTICAST  MTU:1500  Metric:1\n"
"          RX packets:1498792 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 frame:0\n"
"          TX packets:1284980 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 carrier:0\n"
"          collisions:1984 txqueuelen:100\n"
"          RX bytes:485691215 (463.1 Mb)  TX bytes:123951388 (118.2 Mb)\n"
"          Interrupt:11 Base address:0xe800 \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "Optional: Configure any Proxies"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:123
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you access the Internet through a proxy, you might need to set up proxy\n"
"information during the installation. It is very easy to define a proxy: you just\n"
"need to define a variable which contains the proxy server information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:129
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In most cases, you can just define the variables using the server hostname. As\n"
"an example, we assume the proxy is called <c>proxy.gentoo.org</c> and the port \n"
"is <c>8080</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "Defining proxy servers"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:135
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(If the proxy filters HTTP traffic)</comment>\n"
"# <i>export http_proxy=\"http://proxy.gentoo.org:8080\"</i>\n"
"<comment>(If the proxy filters FTP traffic)</comment>\n"
"# <i>export ftp_proxy=\"ftp://proxy.gentoo.org:8080\"</i>\n"
"<comment>(If the proxy filters RSYNC traffic)</comment>\n"
"# <i>export RSYNC_PROXY=\"proxy.gentoo.org:8080\"</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:144
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your proxy requires a username and password, you should use the following\n"
"syntax for the variable:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:148
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding username/password to the proxy variable"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:149
#, no-wrap
msgid "http://<i>username</i>:<i>password</i>@proxy.gentoo.org:8080\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:155
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing the Network"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:159
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You may want to try pinging your ISP's DNS server (found in\n"
"<path>/etc/resolv.conf</path>) and a Web site of your choice, just to make sure \n"
"that your packets are reaching the net, DNS name resolution is working \n"
"correctly, etc.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "Further network testing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>ping -c 3 www.gentoo.org</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:170
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are now able to use your network, you can skip the rest of this\n"
"section and continue with <uri link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=4\">Preparing the\n"
"Disks</uri>. If not, read on.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:179
#, no-wrap
msgid "Automatic Network Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:184
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If the network doesn't work immediately, some installation media allow you to \n"
"use <c>net-setup</c> (for regular or wireless networks), <c>pppoe-setup</c> \n"
"(for ADSL-users) or <c>pptp</c> (for PPTP-users - only available on x86).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:190
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your installation medium does not contain any of these tools or your network\n"
"doesn't function yet, continue with <uri link=\"#doc_chap3\">Manual Network \n"
"Configuration</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:197
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Regular Ethernet users should continue with <uri\n"
"    link=\"#net-setup\">Default: Using net-setup</uri>\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:201
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ADSL users should continue with <uri link=\"#ppp\">Alternative: Using\n"
"    PPP</uri>\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:205
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    PPTP users should continue with <uri link=\"#pptp\">Alternative:\n"
"    Using PPTP</uri>\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "Default: Using net-setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:217
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The simplest way to set up networking if it didn't get configured\n"
"automatically is to run the <c>net-setup</c> script:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:221
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running the net-setup script"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:222
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>net-setup eth0</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:226
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>net-setup</c> will ask you some questions about your network\n"
"environment. When all is done, you should have a working network\n"
"connection. Test your network connection as stated before. If the tests\n"
"are positive, congratulations! You are now ready to install Gentoo. Skip\n"
"the rest of this section and continue with <uri \n"
"link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=4\">Preparing the Disks</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your network still doesn't work, continue with <uri link=\"#doc_chap3\">Manual\n"
"Network Configuration</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternative: Using PPP"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:247
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Assuming you need PPPoE to connect to the internet, the Installation CD (any\n"
"version) has made things easy for you by including <c>ppp</c>. Use the provided\n"
"<c>pppoe-setup</c> script to configure your connection. You will be prompted for\n"
"the ethernet device that is connected to your adsl modem, your username and\n"
"password, the IPs of your DNS servers and if you need a basic firewall or not.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:254
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using ppp"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:255
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>pppoe-setup</i>\n"
"# <i>pppoe-start</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:260
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If something goes wrong, double-check that you correctly typed your username and\n"
"password by looking at <path>/etc/ppp/pap-secrets</path> or \n"
"<path>/etc/ppp/chap-secrets</path> and make sure you are using the right \n"
"ethernet device. If your ethernet device doesn't exist, you will have to load\n"
"the appropriate network modules. In that case you should continue with \n"
"<uri link=\"#doc_chap3\">Manual Network Configuration</uri> as we explain how to\n"
"load the appropriate network modules there.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:270
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If everything worked, continue with <uri link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=4\">Preparing the\n"
"Disks</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:277
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternative: Using PPTP"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><note>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:281
#, no-wrap
msgid "PPTP support is only available for x86\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:285
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you need PPTP support, you can use <c>pptpclient</c> which is provided by our\n"
"Installation CDs. But first you need to make sure that your configuration is \n"
"correct. Edit <path>/etc/ppp/pap-secrets</path> or \n"
"<path>/etc/ppp/chap-secrets</path> so it contains the correct username/password \n"
"combination:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:292
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing /etc/ppp/chap-secrets"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:293
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>nano -w /etc/ppp/chap-secrets</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:297
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then adjust <path>/etc/ppp/options.pptp</path> if necessary:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:300
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing /etc/ppp/options.pptp"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:301
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>nano -w /etc/ppp/options.pptp</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:305
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When all that is done, just run <c>pptp</c> (along with the options you couldn't\n"
"set in <path>options.pptp</path>) to connect the server:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "Connection to a dial-in server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:310
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>pptp &lt;server ip&gt;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:314
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now continue with <uri link=\"?part=1&amp;chap=4\">Preparing the Disks</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:321
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manual Network Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:323
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading the Appropriate Network Modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:327
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When the Installation CD boots, it tries to detect all your hardware devices and\n"
"loads the appropriate kernel modules (drivers) to support your hardware. In the\n"
"vast majority of cases, it does a very good job. However, in some cases,\n"
"it may not auto-load the kernel modules you need.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:334
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If <c>net-setup</c> or <c>pppoe-setup</c> failed, then it is possible that\n"
"your network card wasn't found immediately. This means you may have to load\n"
"the appropriate kernel modules manually.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:340
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To find out what kernel modules we provide for networking, use\n"
"<c>ls</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:344
#, no-wrap
msgid "Searching for provided modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:345
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>ls /lib/modules/`uname -r`/kernel/drivers/net</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:349
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you find a driver for your network card, use <c>modprobe</c> to load\n"
"the kernel module:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:353
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using modprobe to load a kernel module"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:354
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(As an example, we load the pcnet32 module)</comment>\n"
"# <i>modprobe pcnet32</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:359
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To check if your network card is now detected, use <c>ifconfig</c>. A\n"
"detected network card would result in something like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:363
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing availability of your network card, successful"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:364
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>ifconfig eth0</i>\n"
"eth0      Link encap:Ethernet  HWaddr FE:FD:00:00:00:00  \n"
"          BROADCAST NOARP MULTICAST  MTU:1500  Metric:1\n"
"          RX packets:0 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 frame:0\n"
"          TX packets:0 errors:0 dropped:0 overruns:0 carrier:0\n"
"          collisions:0 txqueuelen:0 \n"
"          RX bytes:0 (0.0 b)  TX bytes:0 (0.0 b)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:374
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If however you receive the following error, the network card is not\n"
"detected:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:378
#, no-wrap
msgid "Testing availability of your network card, failed"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:379
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>ifconfig eth0</i>\n"
"eth0: error fetching interface information: Device not found\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:384
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have multiple network cards in your system they are named <e>eth0</e>,\n"
"<e>eth1</e>, etc. Make sure that the network card you want to use works well and\n"
"remember to use the correct naming throughout this document. We will assume that\n"
"the network card <e>eth0</e> is used.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:391
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Assuming that you now have a detected network card, you can \n"
"retry <c>net-setup</c> or <c>pppoe-setup</c> again (which should work \n"
"now), but for the hardcore people amongst you we explain how to configure your \n"
"network manually.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2007.0/hb-install-network.xml:398
#, no-wrap
msgid "Select one of the following sections based on your network setup:\n"
msgstr ""

